channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Learning to Skip the Middle Layers of Transformers
item.description: Conditional computation is a popular strategy to make Transformers more efficient.

item.title: PsyLite Technical Report
item.description: With the rapid development of digital technology, AI-driven psychological counseling has gradually become an important research direction in the field of mental health.

item.title: Response Quality Assessment for Retrieval-Augmented Generation via Conditional Conformal Factuality
item.description: Compared to existing RAG auto-evaluation methods, Conformal-RAG offers statistical guarantees on the quality of refined sub-claims, ensuring response reliability without the need for ground truth answers.

item.title: DBConformer: Dual-Branch Convolutional Transformer for EEG Decoding
item.description: It integrates a temporal Conformer to model long-range temporal dependencies and a spatial Conformer to extract inter-channel interactions, capturing both temporal dynamics and spatial patterns in EEG signals.

item.title: How Good Are Synthetic Requirements ? Evaluating LLM-Generated Datasets for AI4RE
item.description: We investigate four research questions assessing how prompting strategies, automated prompt optimization, and post-generation curation affect data quality across four classification tasks: defect detection, functional vs. non-functional, quality vs. non-quality, and security vs. non-security.

item.title: GPTailor: Large Language Model Pruning Through Layer Cutting and Stitching
item.description: Large language models (LLMs) have shown remarkable capabilities in language understanding and generation.

item.title: Loss-Aware Automatic Selection of Structured Pruning Criteria for Deep Neural Network Acceleration
item.description: This paper presents an efficient Loss-Aware Automatic Selection of Structured Pruning Criteria (LAASP) for slimming and accelerating deep neural networks.

item.title: Disentangled representations of microscopy images
item.description: Microscopy image analysis is fundamental for different applications, from diagnosis to synthetic engineering and environmental monitoring.

item.title: Introducing EG-IPT and ipt~: a novel electric guitar dataset and a new Max/MSP object for real-time classification of instrumental playing techniques
item.description: This paper presents two key contributions to the real-time classification of Instrumental Playing Techniques (IPTs) in the context of NIME and human-machine interactive systems: the EG-IPT dataset and the iptâˆ¼ Max/MSP object.

item.title: Fast and Distributed Equivariant Graph Neural Networks by Virtual Node Learning
item.description: Equivariant Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) have achieved remarkable success across diverse scientific applications.

item.title: SMARTIES: Spectrum-Aware Multi-Sensor Auto-Encoder for Remote Sensing Images
item.description: From optical sensors to microwave radars, leveraging the complementary strengths of remote sensing (RS) sensors is crucial for achieving dense spatio-temporal monitoring of our planet.

item.title: CycleDistill: Bootstrapping Machine Translation using LLMs with Cyclical Distillation
item.description: Large language models (LLMs), despite their ability to perform few-shot machine translation (MT), often lag behind dedicated MT systems trained on parallel corpora, which are crucial for high quality machine translation (MT).

item.title: AnalogNAS-Bench: A NAS Benchmark for Analog In-Memory Computing
item.description: Analog In-memory Computing (AIMC) has emerged as a highly efficient paradigm for accelerating Deep Neural Networks (DNNs), offering significant energy and latency benefits over conventional digital hardware.

item.title: ReasonFlux-PRM: Trajectory-Aware PRMs for Long Chain-of-Thought Reasoning in LLMs
item.description: We adapt ReasonFlux-PRM to support reward supervision under both offline and online settings, including (i) selecting high-quality model distillation data for downstream supervised fine-tuning of smaller models, (ii) providing dense process-level rewards for policy optimization during reinforcement learning, and (iii) enabling reward-guided Best-of-N test-time scaling.

item.title: LongWriter-Zero: Mastering Ultra-Long Text Generation via Reinforcement Learning
item.description: Ultra-long generation by large language models (LLMs) is a widely demanded scenario, yet it remains a significant challenge due to their maximum generation length limit and overall quality degradation as sequence length increases.

item.title: PP-DocBee2: Improved Baselines with Efficient Data for Multimodal Document Understanding
item.description: This report introduces PP-DocBee2, an advanced version of the PP-DocBee, designed to enhance multimodal document understanding.

item.title: TAB: Unified Benchmarking of Time Series Anomaly Detection Methods
item.description: Time series anomaly detection (TSAD) plays an important role in many domains such as finance, transportation, and healthcare.

item.title: Universal Music Representations? Evaluating Foundation Models on World Music Corpora
item.description: Foundation models have revolutionized music information retrieval, but questions remain about their ability to generalize across diverse musical traditions.

item.title: TabArena: A Living Benchmark for Machine Learning on Tabular Data
item.description: We launch TabArena with a public leaderboard, reproducible code, and maintenance protocols to create a living benchmark available at https://tabarena. ai.

item.title: Sparse-Reg: Improving Sample Complexity in Offline Reinforcement Learning using Sparsity
item.description: In this paper, we investigate the use of small datasets in the context of offline reinforcement learning (RL).

item.title: Hunyuan3D 2.5: Towards High-Fidelity 3D Assets Generation with Ultimate Details
item.description: In this report, we present Hunyuan3D 2. 5, a robust suite of 3D diffusion models aimed at generating high-fidelity and detailed textured 3D assets.

item.title: Show-o2: Improved Native Unified Multimodal Models
item.description: Based on a language model, autoregressive modeling and flow matching are natively applied to the language head and flow head, respectively, to facilitate text token prediction and image/video generation.

item.title: Navigating the growing field of research on AI for software testing -- the taxonomy for AI-augmented software testing and an ontology-driven literature survey
item.description: This paper reviews recent research on AI augmentation in software test automation, from no automation to full automation.

item.title: Towards Robust Learning to Optimize with Theoretical Guarantees
item.description: Based on our proposed methodology of aligning OOD problems to InD problems, we also demonstrate that the L2O model's convergence rate in OOD scenarios will deteriorate by an equation of the L2O model's input features.

item.title: Xolver: Multi-Agent Reasoning with Holistic Experience Learning Just Like an Olympiad Team
item.description: Despite impressive progress on complex reasoning, current large language models (LLMs) typically operate in isolation - treating each problem as an independent attempt, without accumulating or integrating experiential knowledge.

item.title: RMIT-ADM+S at the SIGIR 2025 LiveRAG Challenge
item.description: This paper presents the RMIT--ADM+S participation in the SIGIR 2025 LiveRAG Challenge.

item.title: Lecture Video Visual Objects (LVVO) Dataset: A Benchmark for Visual Object Detection in Educational Videos
item.description: We introduce the Lecture Video Visual Objects (LVVO) dataset, a new benchmark for visual object detection in educational video content.

item.title: PeakWeather: MeteoSwiss Weather Station Measurements for Spatiotemporal Deep Learning
item.description: Accurate weather forecasts are essential for supporting a wide range of activities and decision-making processes, as well as mitigating the impacts of adverse weather events.

item.title: Arctic Long Sequence Training: Scalable And Efficient Training For Multi-Million Token Sequences
item.description: ALST supports training Meta's Llama 8B model with 500K sequence length on a single H100 GPU, 3. 7M on a single 8xH100 GPU node, and over 15M on a 4 node cluster, an increase of over 400x compared to the 32K baseline for the latter.

item.title: ZipVoice: Fast and High-Quality Zero-Shot Text-to-Speech with Flow Matching
item.description: Existing large-scale zero-shot text-to-speech (TTS) models deliver high speech quality but suffer from slow inference speeds due to massive parameters.

item.title: Stream-Omni: Simultaneous Multimodal Interactions with Large Language-Vision-Speech Model
item.description: The emergence of GPT-4o-like large multimodal models (LMMs) has raised the exploration of integrating text, vision, and speech modalities to support more flexible multimodal interaction.

item.title: Vine Copulas as Differentiable Computational Graphs
item.description: Vine copulas are sophisticated models for multivariate distributions and are increasingly used in machine learning.

item.title: DETRPose: Real-time end-to-end transformer model for multi-person pose estimation
item.description: The paper presents a family of transformer-based models capable of performing multi-person 2D pose estimation in real-time.

item.title: Self-Supervised Enhancement for Depth from a Lightweight ToF Sensor with Monocular Images
item.description: Depth map enhancement using paired high-resolution RGB images offers a cost-effective solution for improving low-resolution depth data from lightweight ToF sensors.

item.title: AutoVLA: A Vision-Language-Action Model for End-to-End Autonomous Driving with Adaptive Reasoning and Reinforcement Fine-Tuning
item.description: Recent advancements in Vision-Language-Action (VLA) models have shown promise for end-to-end autonomous driving by leveraging world knowledge and reasoning capabilities.

item.title: Membership Inference Attacks as Privacy Tools: Reliability, Disparity and Ensemble
item.description: Membership inference attacks (MIAs) pose a significant threat to the privacy of machine learning models and are widely used as tools for privacy assessment, auditing, and machine unlearning.

item.title: Vector Ontologies as an LLM world view extraction method
item.description: Large Language Models (LLMs) possess intricate internal representations of the world, yet these latent structures are notoriously difficult to interpret or repurpose beyond the original prediction task.

item.title: SAGDA: Open-Source Synthetic Agriculture Data for Africa
item.description: Data scarcity in African agriculture hampers machine learning (ML) model performance, limiting innovations in precision agriculture.

item.title: Automated Risk Management Mechanisms in DeFi Lending Protocols: A Crosschain Comparative Analysis of Aave and Compound
item.description: In contrast, liquidations in v2 have an insignificant impact, which indicates that the most recent v3 protocols have better risk management than the earlier v2 protocols.

item.title: Focusing on Tracks for Online Multi-Object Tracking
item.description: Multi-object tracking (MOT) is a critical task in computer vision, requiring the accurate identification and continuous tracking of multiple objects across video frames.

item.title: M^3-VOS: Multi-Phase, Multi-Transition, and Multi-Scenery Video Object Segmentation
item.description: In light of this, we introduce the concept of phase in segmentation, which categorizes real-world objects based on their visual characteristics and potential morphological and appearance changes.

item.title: BeyondRPC: A Contrastive and Augmentation-Driven Framework for Robust Point Cloud Understanding
item.description: Robust perception of 3D point clouds remains a significant challenge in real-world environments where sensor data is often corrupted.

item.title: TCANet: A Temporal Convolutional Attention Network for Motor Imagery EEG Decoding
item.description: This study proposes the Temporal Convolutional Attention Network (TCANet), a novel end-to-end model that hierarchically captures spatiotemporal dependencies by progressively integrating local, fused, and global features.

item.title: A Review of the Long Horizon Forecasting Problem in Time Series Analysis
item.description: The long horizon forecasting (LHF) problem has come up in the time series literature for over the last 35 years or so.

item.title: Real-Time Per-Garment Virtual Try-On with Temporal Consistency for Loose-Fitting Garments
item.description: This enhances the robustness of semantic map estimation under loose-fitting garments during garment-specific dataset generation.

item.title: Revisiting Clustering of Neural Bandits: Selective Reinitialization for Mitigating Loss of Plasticity
item.description: Clustering of Bandits (CB) methods enhance sequential decision-making by grouping bandits into clusters based on similarity and incorporating cluster-level contextual information, demonstrating effectiveness and adaptability in applications like personalized streaming recommendations.

item.title: MatchPlant: An Open-Source Pipeline for UAV-Based Single-Plant Detection and Data Extraction
item.description: Accurate identification of individual plants from unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) images is essential for advancing high-throughput phenotyping and supporting data-driven decision-making in plant breeding.

item.title: FlexRAG: A Flexible and Comprehensive Framework for Retrieval-Augmented Generation
item.description: Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) plays a pivotal role in modern large language model applications, with numerous existing frameworks offering a wide range of functionalities to facilitate the development of RAG systems.

item.title: OpenUnlearning: Accelerating LLM Unlearning via Unified Benchmarking of Methods and Metrics
item.description: Robust unlearning is crucial for safely deploying large language models (LLMs) in environments where data privacy, model safety, and regulatory compliance must be ensured.

item.title: Learning Encodings by Maximizing State Distinguishability: Variational Quantum Error Correction
item.description: Quantum error correction is crucial for protecting quantum information against decoherence.
